---
description: Apply TypeScript naming conventions for files, symbols, and booleans across backend/frontend
globs: volley-app-backend/**/*.ts, volley-app-frontend/**/*.ts, volley-app-frontend/**/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---
Classes and Interfaces:
- Use PascalCase for names
- Use nouns or noun phrases

Functions and Methods:
- Use camelCase for names
- Use verbs for actions
- Use nouns for value-returning
- Prefix booleans with is, has, should
- No anemic models

Variables and Properties:
- Descriptive, no abbreviations
- Plurals for collections
- Constants in UPPER_SNAKE_CASE

Files and Folders:
- One responsibility per file
- Feature-based organization frontend
- Match framework conventions
